{"title_page": "Halla Vilhj\u00e1lmsd\u00f3ttir", "text_new": "{{icelandic name|Halla}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2016}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = \n| image         = \n| imagesize     = \n| caption       = \n| birth_name    = Halla Vilhj\u00e1lmsd\u00f3ttir\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|1982|01|30|df=y}}\n| birth_place   = [[Reykjav\u00edk]], [[Iceland]]\n| death_date    = \n| death_place   = \n| othername     = Hatla Williams, Halla Williams, Halla Koppel\n| years_active  = 2002-\n| spouse        =  \n| website       = {{URL|www.hallawilliams.com}} \n}}\n'''Halla Vilhj\u00e1lmsd\u00f3ttir''' (born 30 January 1982) is an [[Icelandic language|Icelandic]] television, film actress, and singer.\n\n==Biography==\nHalla graduated in 2004 from the [[Guildford School of Acting]] in [[Guildford, Surrey]], she worked in this time for [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]] and the [[BBC]].<ref>[http://www.visir.is/hreindis-komst-inn-i-draumaskolann/article/2010529149973 V\u00edsir - Hreind\u00eds komst inn \u00ed draumask\u00f3lann]</ref>\n\n===Movie career===\nIn 2002, Halla earned a role in the Icelandic drama film ''Gemsar'', and starred in her first lead role in the 2006 comedy film ''\u00c1ram\u00f3taskaup''. One year later, she portrayed Beta in Icelandic fantasy comedy film ''[[Astr\u00f3p\u00eda]]''.<ref>[http://kisi.is/movies/astropia-2007 Astr\u00f3p\u00eda (2007)]</ref> In 2009 she earned her first international role, playing a prisoner in the British mystery thriller film ''[[Ghost Machine (film)|Ghost Machine]]'' under the pseudonym Hatla Williams.\n\n===Television career===\nHalla hosted the 2006 Icelandic version of ''[[The X Factor (TV series)|X Factor]]''.<ref>[http://www.dv.is/frettir/2009/10/21/halla-i-netkosningu-fyrir-undankeppni-eurovision-i-svithjod-myndband/ DV.is - Fr\u00e9tt - Halla \u00ed netkosningu fyrir undankeppni Eurovision \u00ed Sv\u00ed\u00fej\u00f3\u00f0-Myndband]</ref> In 2008, she played one of the lead roles in the Icelandic Crime television series ''Mannavei\u00f0ar''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.fil.is/cgi-bin/WebObjects/FIL.woa/wa/member?id=1000001&memberID=1000421 |title=Halla Vilhj\u00e1lmsd\u00f3ttir - F\u00cdL - Fors\u00ed\u00f0a |access-date=30 May 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722021313/http://www.fil.is/cgi-bin/WebObjects/FIL.woa/wa/member?id=1000001&memberID=1000421 |archive-date=22 July 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> She has played various roles in TV comedies and sitcoms.\n\n===Stage career===\nShe played the lead role in the Threepenny Opera at the Icelandic National Theatre, and the lead role of Arial in Footloose, among others.\n\n===Mountaineering career===\nHalla has summited four of the [[Seven Summits]] - [[Aconcagua]] 6,960m, [[Mount Elbrus]] 5,642m, [[Kilimanjaro]] 5,895m and [[Mount Vinson]] 4,892m.<ref>http://grapevine.is/news/2013/12/27/icelander-reaches-antarcticas-tallest-peak-on-christmas-eve/</ref>\n\n===Music career===\nThe [[Soprano]] singer performed the song Roses in the fourth Semi-Final of the [[Iceland in the Eurovision Song Contest 2009|Iceland preliminaries]] for the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2009]].<ref>[http://www.eurovisionary.com/taxonomy/term/2717 S\u00f6ngvakeppni Sj\u00f3nvarpsins 4th Semifinal: Icelandic Final Songs Confirmed]</ref> Halla is the female lead singer of the Icelandic Pop band Villimadur.<ref>[http://www.villimadur.is/ Vili Madur]</ref>\n\n===Personal life===\nIn 2007, she was briefly in a relationship with [[Hollywood]] star [[Jude Law]].{{cn|date=December 2019}}\n\nIn 2014 she married Colombian banker Harry Koppel in Bogota;<ref>http://www.mbl.is/smartland/stars/2014/12/15/halla_vilhjalms_gifti_sig_i_kolumbiu/</ref> they have one daughter (Louisa Koppel) born on 23 September 2015 <ref>http://www.mbl.is/smartland/stars/2015/09/23/halla_koppel_ordin_mamma/</ref>\n\nIn 2015 she started an MBA at the University of Oxford with a GMAT score above 700.<ref>http://www.ft.com/cms/s/2/322eec9c-606f-11e5-9846-de406ccb37f2.html#axzz3w7k90fi2</ref>\n\n===Dubbing===\n* [[101 Dalmatians: The Series|101 Dalmatians]] - Rolly\n* Cinderella - Suzy\n* [[The Lion King 2: Simba's Pride]] - Vitani\n* Pinocchio - Dutch Puppet, French Puppet, and Russian Puppet\n* The Jungle Book - Shanti\n* [[The Little Mermaid 2: Return to the Sea]] - Melody\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" width=\"33\"|Year\n! rowspan=\"2\"|Film\n! colspan=\"7\"|Credited as\n|-\n! width=65 |[[Actor]]\n! width=65 |Host\n! Role\n|-align=\"center\"\n| rowspan=\"1\"| 2002\n| align=\"left\"| ''Gemsar''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| align=\"left\"| Kristin\n|-align=\"center\"\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2006\n| align=\"left\"| ''\u00c1ram\u00f3taskaup 2006''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{No}}\n| align=\"left\"| \n|-align=\"center\" \n| align=\"left\"| ''[[The X Factor (TV series)|The X Factor]]''\n| {{No}}\n| {{yes}}\n| align=\"left\"| \n|-align=\"center\" \n| align=\"left\"| ''Venni P\u00e1er''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| align=\"left\"| Lilja\n|-align=\"center\"\n| rowspan=\"1\"| 2007\n| align=\"left\"| ''[[Astr\u00f3p\u00eda]]''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{No}}\n| align=\"left\"| Beta\n|-align=\"center\"\n| rowspan=\"1\"| 2008\n| align=\"left\"| ''Mannavei\u00f0ar''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| align=\"left\"| (Television series)\n|-align=\"center\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2009\n| align=\"left\"| ''[[Ghost Machine (film)|Ghost Machine]]''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| align=\"left\"| Prisoner K (as Hatla Williams)\n|-align=\"center\"\n| align=\"left\"| ''[[Ghost Machine (film)|The Making of 'Ghost Machine]]''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| align=\"left\"| Herself\n|-align=\"center\"\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|id=1146464|name=Halla Vilhj\u00e1lmsd\u00f3ttir}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vilhjalmsdottir, Halla}}\n[[Category:1982 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Icelandic voice actresses|Halla Vilhjalmsdottir]]\n[[Category:Icelandic television personalities|Halla Vilhjalmsdottir]]\n[[Category:People from Reykjav\u00edk|Halla Vilhjalmsdottir]]\n[[Category:Icelandic film actresses|Halla Vilhjalmsdottir]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the Guildford School of Acting]]\n[[Category:Icelandic female singers|Halla Vilhjalmsdottir]]\n[[Category:Icelandic expatriates in England|Halla Vilhjalmsdottir]]\n[[Category:Icelandic television actresses|Halla Vilhjalmsdottir]]\n[[Category:21st-century Icelandic actresses|Halla Vilhjalmsdottir]]\n[[Category:Actors from Reykjav\u00edk|Halla Vilhjalmsdottir]]\n[[Category:21st-century women singers]]\n", "text_old": "{{icelandic name|Halla}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2016}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = \n| image         = \n| imagesize     = \n| caption       = \n| birth_name    = Halla Vilhj\u00e1lmsd\u00f3ttir\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|1982|01|30|df=y}}\n| birth_place   = [[Reykjav\u00edk]], [[Iceland]]\n| death_date    = \n| death_place   = \n| othername     = Hatla Williams, Halla Williams, Halla Koppel\n| years_active  = 2002-\n| spouse        =  \n| website       = {{URL|www.hallawilliams.com}} \n}}\n'''Halla Vilhj\u00e1lmsd\u00f3ttir''' (born 30 January 1982) is an Icelandic television, film actress, and singer.\n\n==Biography==\nHalla graduated in 2004 from the [[Guildford School of Acting]] in [[Guildford, Surrey]], she worked in this time for [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]] and the [[BBC]].<ref>[http://www.visir.is/hreindis-komst-inn-i-draumaskolann/article/2010529149973 V\u00edsir - Hreind\u00eds komst inn \u00ed draumask\u00f3lann]</ref>\n\n===Movie career===\nIn 2002, Halla earned a role in the Icelandic drama film ''Gemsar'', and starred in her first lead role in the 2006 comedy film ''\u00c1ram\u00f3taskaup''. One year later, she portrayed Beta in Icelandic fantasy comedy film ''[[Astr\u00f3p\u00eda]]''.<ref>[http://kisi.is/movies/astropia-2007 Astr\u00f3p\u00eda (2007)]</ref> In 2009 she earned her first international role, playing a prisoner in the British mystery thriller film ''[[Ghost Machine (film)|Ghost Machine]]'' under the pseudonym Hatla Williams.\n\n===Television career===\nHalla hosted the 2006 Icelandic version of ''[[The X Factor (TV series)|X Factor]]''.<ref>[http://www.dv.is/frettir/2009/10/21/halla-i-netkosningu-fyrir-undankeppni-eurovision-i-svithjod-myndband/ DV.is - Fr\u00e9tt - Halla \u00ed netkosningu fyrir undankeppni Eurovision \u00ed Sv\u00ed\u00fej\u00f3\u00f0-Myndband]</ref> In 2008, she played one of the lead roles in the Icelandic Crime television series ''Mannavei\u00f0ar''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.fil.is/cgi-bin/WebObjects/FIL.woa/wa/member?id=1000001&memberID=1000421 |title=Halla Vilhj\u00e1lmsd\u00f3ttir - F\u00cdL - Fors\u00ed\u00f0a |access-date=30 May 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722021313/http://www.fil.is/cgi-bin/WebObjects/FIL.woa/wa/member?id=1000001&memberID=1000421 |archive-date=22 July 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> She has played various roles in TV comedies and sitcoms.\n\n===Stage career===\nShe played the lead role in the Threepenny Opera at the Icelandic National Theatre, and the lead role of Arial in Footloose, among others.\n\n===Mountaineering career===\nHalla has summited four of the [[Seven Summits]] - [[Aconcagua]] 6,960m, [[Mount Elbrus]] 5,642m, [[Kilimanjaro]] 5,895m and [[Mount Vinson]] 4,892m.<ref>http://grapevine.is/news/2013/12/27/icelander-reaches-antarcticas-tallest-peak-on-christmas-eve/</ref>\n\n===Music career===\nThe [[Soprano]] singer performed the song Roses in the fourth Semi-Final of the [[Iceland in the Eurovision Song Contest 2009|Iceland preliminaries]] for the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2009]].<ref>[http://www.eurovisionary.com/taxonomy/term/2717 S\u00f6ngvakeppni Sj\u00f3nvarpsins 4th Semifinal: Icelandic Final Songs Confirmed]</ref> Halla is the female lead singer of the Icelandic Pop band Villimadur.<ref>[http://www.villimadur.is/ Vili Madur]</ref>\n\n===Personal life===\nIn 2007, she was briefly in a relationship with [[Hollywood]] star [[Jude Law]].{{cn|date=December 2019}}\n\nIn 2014 she married Colombian banker Harry Koppel in Bogota;<ref>http://www.mbl.is/smartland/stars/2014/12/15/halla_vilhjalms_gifti_sig_i_kolumbiu/</ref> they have one daughter (Louisa Koppel) born on 23 September 2015 <ref>http://www.mbl.is/smartland/stars/2015/09/23/halla_koppel_ordin_mamma/</ref>\n\nIn 2015 she started an MBA at the University of Oxford with a GMAT score above 700.<ref>http://www.ft.com/cms/s/2/322eec9c-606f-11e5-9846-de406ccb37f2.html#axzz3w7k90fi2</ref>\n\n===Dubbing===\n* [[101 Dalmatians: The Series|101 Dalmatians]] - Rolly\n* Cinderella - Suzy\n* [[The Lion King 2: Simba's Pride]] - Vitani\n* Pinocchio - Dutch Puppet, French Puppet, and Russian Puppet\n* The Jungle Book - Shanti\n* [[The Little Mermaid 2: Return to the Sea]] - Melody\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" width=\"33\"|Year\n! rowspan=\"2\"|Film\n! colspan=\"7\"|Credited as\n|-\n! width=65 |[[Actor]]\n! width=65 |Host\n! Role\n|-align=\"center\"\n| rowspan=\"1\"| 2002\n| align=\"left\"| ''Gemsar''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| align=\"left\"| Kristin\n|-align=\"center\"\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2006\n| align=\"left\"| ''\u00c1ram\u00f3taskaup 2006''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{No}}\n| align=\"left\"| \n|-align=\"center\" \n| align=\"left\"| ''[[The X Factor (TV series)|The X Factor]]''\n| {{No}}\n| {{yes}}\n| align=\"left\"| \n|-align=\"center\" \n| align=\"left\"| ''Venni P\u00e1er''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| align=\"left\"| Lilja\n|-align=\"center\"\n| rowspan=\"1\"| 2007\n| align=\"left\"| ''[[Astr\u00f3p\u00eda]]''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{No}}\n| align=\"left\"| Beta\n|-align=\"center\"\n| rowspan=\"1\"| 2008\n| align=\"left\"| ''Mannavei\u00f0ar''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| align=\"left\"| (Television series)\n|-align=\"center\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2009\n| align=\"left\"| ''[[Ghost Machine (film)|Ghost Machine]]''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| align=\"left\"| Prisoner K (as Hatla Williams)\n|-align=\"center\"\n| align=\"left\"| ''[[Ghost Machine (film)|The Making of 'Ghost Machine]]''\n| {{yes}}\n|